    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium-risk model. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 testing and is accepted because the validation scenario is identical to the COU and no extrapolation is required. The quantitative validation metric E/uval is below 1.96 for all QoIs across all three FEA platforms. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support regulatory submission. Note: this package conforms to the Minimal profile; the signature workflow is pending and the package hash is recorded for integrity tracking pending execution of the institutional signing ceremony.",
